Descendants Must Override Item?:Set Method

Short Name: Set MustOverride?

Requires: Base Development System

Class: LVClassLibrary Methods

To Use: Create a method.

Determines whether descendant classes must override the member VI specified by Dynamic Member VI.

This method is similar to the Require descendant classes to override this dynamic dispatch VI checkbox of the Item Settings page of the Class Properties dialog box.

Parameters

Data typeNameRequiredDescription
Dynamic Member VIYesSpecifies the member VI that you want to set whether descendant classes must override.
Must Call Parent?YesSpecifies whether the descendant VIs of the member VI must call the member VI.

Remarks

The following table lists the characteristics of this method.
